        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "improve: simplify PR context and evidence",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nThe PR template and external-contributor gate currently require a rigid field-by-field proof form. That duplicates information, makes otherwise clear PRs harder to read, and asks automation to judge proof from prose instead of inspecting the code, tests, and CI.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nReplace the field-level proof form with two authored sections: `What Problem This Solves` and `Evidence`. The shared gate checks only that those sections contain visible, meaningful content, while preserving a temporary fallback for open PRs that still use the legacy structured body. Barnacle now uses the same parsing behavior as the gate.\n\n## User Impact\n\nAuthors can write concise PRs that explain intent, design, impact, and the most useful validation evidence. Reviewers and AI can use that context while relying on the diff, tests, and CI as the source of truth for correctness.\n\n## Evidence\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs test/scripts/real-behavior-proof-policy.test.ts test/scripts/barnacle-auto-response.test.ts test/scripts/real-behavior-proof-check.test.ts`\n  - 84 tests passed.\n- `./node_modules/.bin/oxfmt --check` across all changed files.\n- `git diff --check`\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local --parallel-tests \"<focused tooling command>\"`\n  - Clean: no accepted or actionable findings.\n",
